Outcomes Dashboard Layout

Jul 19, 2023•Knowledge

Package Availability
Indicates which SalesLoft package(s) include the feature referenced in this knowledge article.
Content

The Outcomes Dashboard provides insights into outcomes and goal progress for teams and individual representatives. This information can play an important part in coaching team members, as it can help you determine which reps are falling behind and where to best focus your efforts to achieve your sales goals.

 

If you have the Outcomes View permission enabled, the Outcomes Dashboard will be the first page you see after clicking on Coaching. It will be the default page upon accessing Coaching from the top navigation.


Things to Note: If you do not have the Outcomes View permission enabled, the Outcomes link will not be available for selection. In this case, the default page upon clicking Coaching from the top navigation will be the existing 1-on-1 coaching page.


 

In this article, we will break down each section of the Outcomes Dashboard, including:

  • Outcomes Dashboard Layout
  • Team Outcomes List
  • Rep Outcomes List
 

Outcomes Dashboard Layout

Each section of the Outcomes Dashboard represents a data point of your outcomes, including goal progress for groups, reps, and more.

 
 
  1. Filters: You can use these filters to change how information is displayed on the dashboard.
    • Date range
    • Group
  2. Display Details: This display changes when you change the date range filter. For example, “Displaying monthly goals for this month” is based on the “Date: This Month” range selection.
  3. Add/Remove Panels: Allows you to select and order (by drag and drop) which goal panels are shown on the outcomes dashboard. 
    • Things to Note: Only three panels can be displayed at a time.
  4. Goal Panels: The information shown is intended to help quickly spot which goals are on track or not as well as reasons why that might be happening. Add or remove these panels to display the top three outcomes you care about most. 
  5. Explore and Compare: This section breaks down the factors that drive outcomes and efficiency.
    • Highlights: Explores team and rep trends as well as additional factors that influence outcome results through visualizations of data.
      • Top Teams: Compares teams with the highest total outcomes.
      • Top Reps: Compares outcome results to effort across reps.
      • Contact Conversion Funnel: Shows how successful prospecting efforts are to the overall sales process.
    • Edit Goals: Allows you to adjust what targets each rep must achieve by the end of the period.
    • Teams: A subset of data including several reps.
    • Reps: Each individual contributor on a team.
 

Team Outcomes List

The Teams section serves as a tool for you to analyze outcomes, efforts, and goal attainment across your defined Salesloft groups. 

 

Things to Note: If your team has not set up any groups, this tab will not be available.

 

This section displays metrics specific to each group, along with in-line charts showcasing the progress towards the set goals for the given period. By clicking on a team's name, you can access the Coaching team view, filtered specifically for that team.

 

Some metrics will be visible with an in-line chart (also known as a chart within the table). The in-line chart represents goal progress and it will only appear if a goal has been established. It displays a bar indicating the percentage of progress made toward the goal based on actual achievements. If the goal is met or exceeded, the progress bar will be colored gold; otherwise, it will be colored purple.

 

The Team Outcomes list includes the following metrics:

  • Meetings Booked
  • Opportunities Created
  • Pipeline
  • Closed Won
  • Win Rate
  • New Pipeline Added
  • Opportunity Conversion Rate
  • Meeting Conversion Rate
  • Activities per Day
  • Total Activities
  • Successes
  • Activities per Success
  • Activities per Opportunity
  • Activities per Meeting
  • People Touched
 


 

Rep Outcomes List

The Reps section lets you analyze and track outcomes, efforts, and goal attainment for each sales representative. 

 

This section presents metrics specific to individual reps, complemented by in-line charts displaying the progress toward their goals during the designated period. 

 

Click the name of a rep to view that rep's dedicated 1-on-1 Coaching detail page.

 

The available metrics for display in this section include:

  • Meetings Booked
  • Opportunities Created
  • Pipeline
  • Closed Won
  • New Pipeline Added
  • Opportunity Conversion Rate
  • Meeting Conversion Rate
  • Activities per Day
  • Total Activities
  • Successes
  • Activities per Success
  • Activities per Opportunity
  • Activities per Meeting
  • Activities per Closed Won Deal
  • People Touched
  • Call Duration per Day
  • Connect Rate
  • Reply Rate
  • % On-Time Steps
  • Emails Sent
  • Calls Logged
  • Integration Steps
 
 

 

If you hover over any data cells for the Meetings Booked Column, you’ll see an option to View Details. Clicking the cell will bring up an additional screen with a list of all of the meetings booked for that rep in the selected period. This list includes meeting details similar to which is found on the Person and Account page activity feed.
